"{\"uid\": \"vaildaily.com-news-val-constien-punches-ticket-to-paris-olympics-with-historic-performance-at-u-s-track-and-field-trials\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"News|Jun 28, 2024  rsederquist@vaildaily.com  Val Constien punched her ticket to a second Olympic Games with a historic performance at the U.S. Track and Field Trials on Thursday night in Eugene, Oregon.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 196, \"end\": 202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"score\": 0.5999993137400566, \"rank\": 0.6666685727631518, \"text\": \"Oregon\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The former Battle Mountain runner won the 3,000-meter steeplechase in 9 minutes, 3.22 seconds, establishing a new trials record.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 216, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Battle_Mountain\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.473020632198418e-21, \"text\": \"Battle Mountain\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Battle_Mountain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Battle_Mountain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Therun also made the 28-year-old the third-fastest U.S. steeplechaser of all-time.\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 416, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have already done it once before, but this time is just so sweet,\\\" the 2021 Olympiantold assembled mediaafter her 11-second personal best.\", \"from\": 418, \"to\": 559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Especially considering how hard last year was.\\\"\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Constienstruggled with injuries and illnessafter her Tokyo Olympic berth.It wasn't until April of 2023that she received her first professional contract.\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9998508169968273, \"rank\": 0.0001124125001942493, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just a week after signing with Nike, however,she blew out her ACL comingoff the water jump at herDiamond League debut in Doha, Qatar.\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\", \"score\": 0.9252357522062247, \"rank\": 0.08080561912526064, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\"}, {\"begin\": 825, \"end\": 828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anterior_cruciate_ligament\", \"score\": 0.9940707199567503, \"rank\": 0.005964646100485592, \"text\": \"ACL\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\", \"Q39888\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anterior_cruciate_ligament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anterior_cruciate_ligament\"}, {\"begin\": 884, \"end\": 888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 0.99999734678192, \"rank\": 2.65322473052553e-06, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}, {\"begin\": 890, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999999999481588, \"rank\": 5.1728675780313596e-11, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"OnMay 23, she had double knee surgeryat the Steadman Clinic in Vail.\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 941, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Steadman\", \"score\": 0.9999996619990842, \"rank\": 3.380006170086051e-07, \"text\": \"Steadman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Steadman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Steadman\"}, {\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vail_Ski_Resort\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.748100364059231e-36, \"text\": \"Vail\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vail_Ski_Resort\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vail_Ski_Resort\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She went on her first run in September.\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not think I was going to be here, to be perfectly honest,\\\" Constien said when asked if the looming date of the Olympic Trials was a stressor during her rehab.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1125, \"end\": 1139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.8581582794956577, \"rank\": 0.038961038961052005, \"text\": \"Olympic Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was like, well, it's a bummer I am going to miss 2024, but at least I will be healthy for 2025.\\\"\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Constien characterized her recovery, which she chronicled on Youtube, as a \\\"very slow and arduous process.\\\"\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1335, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.871026475661737e-50, \"text\": \"Youtube\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I never did anything crazy,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not push anything.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just listened to my body and I did not have any hiccups along the way.\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, really lucky.\\\"\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"April 2023- Constien receives first professional contract  May 5, 2023- Tears ACL in Diamond League debut in Doha, Qatar, one week after signing with Nike.\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1627, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 3.663429246136132e-12, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1651, \"end\": 1655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 0.99999734678192, \"rank\": 2.65322473052553e-06, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}, {\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999999999481588, \"rank\": 5.1728675780313596e-11, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}, {\"begin\": 1692, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\", \"score\": 0.9252357522062247, \"rank\": 0.08080561912526064, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Nike\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"May 23, 2023- Undergoes double knee surgery at The Steadman Clinic in Vail  September, 2023- Constien goes on her first run post-surgery.\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1750, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Steadman\", \"score\": 0.9999996619990842, \"rank\": 3.380006170086051e-07, \"text\": \"Steadman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Steadman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Steadman\"}, {\"begin\": 1769, \"end\": 1773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vail_Ski_Resort\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.748100364059231e-36, \"text\": \"Vail\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vail_Ski_Resort\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vail_Ski_Resort\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"April 15, 2024- Constien runs in her first race since her injury, running 4:12.97 in the 1500-meters at the Bryan Clay Invitational.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1946, \"end\": 1956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryan Clay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"May 11, 2024- Constien qualifies for the U.S. Olympic Trials with a 9:27.22 steeplechase - her first steeplechase since the Doha injury.\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 2108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2018, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.8581582794956577, \"rank\": 0.038961038961052005, \"text\": \"Olympic Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\"}, {\"begin\": 2096, \"end\": 2100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 0.99999734678192, \"rank\": 2.65322473052553e-06, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"May 25, 2024- Constien sets a four-second personal best at the Prefontaine Classic, running 9:14.29  June 27, 2024- Constien becomes the third-fastest U.S. steeplechaser of all-time, running 9:03.22 to win the U.S. Olympic Track and Field Trials in a new trials record.\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After opening her season with a1500-meter run at the Bryan Clay Invitational in April, the 28-year-old thought the trials was a possibility.\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2434, \"end\": 2444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryan Clay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even after notching the trials standard with a9:27.22 win at the Track Festin Los Angeles on May 11 - her first steeplechase since Doha -  she remained relatively low key.\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2653, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 0.99999734678192, \"rank\": 2.65322473052553e-06, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't until she set a personal best of9:14.29 run at the PrefontaineClassic that she raised her expectations from just being aparticipant to being a contender.\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think taking that pressure off and focusing on being healthy and doing everything right was how I got to this point,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2989, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I listened to the surgeons' advice and that patience paid off.\\\"\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her patience paid off in Thursday's race, too.\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aftercruising through the prelims on Monday, Constien predicted sub 9:10 would be required for finishing in the top-3 to make the U.S. team.\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Annie Rodenfels was the early leader, dragging a slew of women through the first kilometer in 3:00.\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3245, \"end\": 3250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Annie_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999996476045164, \"rank\": 3.523957227722938e-07, \"text\": \"Annie\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Annie_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Annie_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though the group was nearly on American record pace, Constien said she wasn't paying attention to the clock.\", \"from\": 3346, \"to\": 3459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3382, \"end\": 3390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999947285687, \"rank\": 5.268512716606573e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was just telling myself that I believed in myself and I needed to be relaxed,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3552, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Courtney Wayment, who finished one place behind Constien and missed qualifying in 2021, set the tone through the second third of the race as Constien sat right on her hip in second.\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3554, \"end\": 3562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.374066032817301e-17, \"text\": \"Courtney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My plan was to run with whoever was at the front and then try to win.\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not even look at the clock,\\\" Constien said.\", \"from\": 3808, \"to\": 3857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was just racing.\\\"\", \"from\": 3858, \"to\": 3878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Coming into the bell lap, 31-year-old Marisa Howard surged into the lead.\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3918, \"end\": 3931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marisa_Howard\", \"score\": 0.9999995357239809, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marisa Howard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marisa_Howard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marisa_Howard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NCAA champion Olivia Markezich also made a bid as Constien nearly was tripped up going over the first-curve barrier.\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 4070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3954, \"end\": 3967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999912206476, \"rank\": 8.779057920103777e-09, \"text\": \"NCAA champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3968, \"end\": 3974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olivia_Dunham\", \"score\": 0.9999981188902396, \"rank\": 1.8811123257036442e-06, \"text\": \"Olivia\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olivia_Dunham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olivia_Dunham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Edwards-native found space on the outside and bolted into the lead for good with 300 meters remaining.\", \"from\": 4071, \"to\": 4177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew if I was in the mix in the last 300, it would be pretty tough to beat me,\\\" said Constien, who closed in an astonishing 2:54 for the last 1,000-meters and 65 seconds for the last lap.\", \"from\": 4179, \"to\": 4369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very confident in my kick, so I knew I had it in me.\\\"\", \"from\": 4370, \"to\": 4429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Markezich landed awkwardly off the water barrier, opening the way for Wayment (9:06.50) to take silver and Howard (9:07.14) the bronze.\", \"from\": 4431, \"to\": 4566, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Just complete disbelief,\\\"said Howard, who came into the race with a previous best of 9:22.\", \"from\": 4568, \"to\": 4659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew I had a big one in me, it was just a matter of putting it together on the day.\\\"\", \"from\": 4659, \"to\": 4746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew it was going to be fast,\\\" Constien said.\", \"from\": 4748, \"to\": 4796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Did I think i was going to run 9:03?\", \"from\": 4797, \"to\": 4834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No, but I mean I feel like I am just starting to reach my potential and figure out how good I am, so hopefully I can just keep it going.\\\"\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 4972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Constien's meteoric rise puts her in serious podium contention at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 4974, \"to\": 5059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not going to think that far ahead,\\\" she said when asked about medaling in August.\", \"from\": 5061, \"to\": 5148, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just going to go back to Boulder, get back to work, do some training, try to feel good and we will see what happens.\\\"\", \"from\": 5149, \"to\": 5272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5180, \"end\": 5187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boulder\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.150795554415144e-33, \"text\": \"Boulder\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boulder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boulder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The steeplechase is a crazy event,\\\" she continued.\", \"from\": 5274, \"to\": 5325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"People fall down, people get back up\\u2026you never know what can happen.\\\"\", \"from\": 5326, \"to\": 5396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dec 6, 2025    Dec 6, 2025  Dec 5, 2025  Dec 5, 2025  Dec 5, 2025  Dec 3, 2025    Dec 2, 2025  Dec 3, 2025  Dec 4, 2025  Dec 3, 2025  Chateau Beaver Creek is a luxury, self-managed HOA/Residence Club and is looking for full-time, year-round team members: Bellmen - $20-\\u2026  We are seeking a skilled Plumbing & HVAC Service Technician who brings a strong team-player mentality and a commitment to\\u2026  Hiring Immediately!\", \"from\": 5400, \"to\": 5815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5542, \"end\": 5554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beaver_Creek_Resort\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.938193093221906e-52, \"text\": \"Beaver Creek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beaver_Creek_Resort\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beaver_Creek_Resort\"}, {\"begin\": 5581, \"end\": 5584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homeowner_association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"HOA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homeowner_association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homeowner_association\"}, {\"begin\": 5697, \"end\": 5705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plumbing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Plumbing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plumbing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plumbing\"}, {\"